OL,6,FEverleigh's mother then returned home
OL,7,Fthe next morning and discovered her
OL,8,Fseriously injured and called the
OL,9,Femergency services.
OL,11,FHolford appeared 'not unduly
OL,12,Fconcerned' and continued to download
OL,13,Fand play games on his phone while
OL,14,FEverleigh was being cared for, Ms
OL,15,FLedward said.
OL,17,FEverleigh suffered brain injuries,
OL,18,Fbone fractures, bruising to her face
OL,19,Fand atrophy to her eyes, causing her
OL,20,Fto go blind.
