OL,6,F"In truth, the decision to leave the
OL,7,Fchild with her father in the
OL,8,Fcircumstances was a perfectly normal,
OL,9,Frational decision.
OL,11,F"It was tragic; it has caused her to
OL,12,Ffeel as she does, responsible in some
OL,13,Fway for her daughter's death.
OL,15,F"The responsibility for that death
OL,16,Flies squarely with the offender, and
OL,17,Fnobody else."
